cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with pose estimation using a neural network approach and specifically focuses on face pose estimation and heart segmentation in 3D CT images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of Graph Transformer Networks (GTN) and Multi Layer Perceptron (MLP) for regression, which falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Back Propagation (BP) for globally tuning the CPR model also suggests the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of 3D CT images for heart segmentation suggests the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
